<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<style>
    body {
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #000;
        margin: 40px;
        font-size: 11pt;
    }
    h1 {
        text-align: center;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #000;
        padding-bottom: 10px;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
    }
    h2 {
        border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;
        color: #2c3e50;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }
    table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin: 20px 0;
    }
    th, td {
        border: 1px solid #000;
        padding: 8px;
        text-align: left;
    }
    th {
        background-color: #f2f2f2;
    }
    .mermaid-desc {
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
        padding: 15px;
        border: 1px dashed #999;
        font-family: "Courier New", Courier, monospace;
        font-size: 10pt;
    }
</style>
<title>Corrected ER Diagram Specification - KaviCakes</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Corrected Entity-Relationship (ER) Specification</h1>

<p><strong>Project:</strong> KaviCakes Management System</p>
<p><strong>Document:</strong> Database Architectural Specification</p>

<hr>

<h2>1. Refined Entity List & Attributes</h2>

<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Entity</th>
            <th>Primary Attributes</th>
            <th>Relationship Context</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>customer</strong></td>
            <td>id, name, email, phone, loyaltyPoints</td>
            <td>Parent to Order, Cart, Notification, Feedback.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>orders</strong></td>
            <td>id, status, total, paymentStatus, deliveryDate</td>
            <td>Linked to Customer (N:1), OrderItem (1:N), Payment (1:1).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>orderitem</strong></td>
            <td>id, quantity, unitPrice</td>
            <td>Bridge between <code>orders</code> and <code>cakevariant</code>.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>cakevariant</strong></td>
            <td>id, price, sizeId, shapeId, flavorId</td>
            <td>Specific SKU of a cake containing size/shape/flavor.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>cake</strong></td>
            <td>id, name, description, categoryId</td>
            <td>Main product item (Parent of variants).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>payment</strong></td>
            <td>id, proofImage, status, verifiedAt</td>
            <td>Tracks financial clearance for an Order (1:1).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>transaction</strong></td>
            <td>id, type, amount, date, cashbookId</td>
            <td>Logs physical cash flow movement (Linked to Order/Payment).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>cashbook</strong></td>
            <td>id, date, openingBalance, closingBalance</td>
            <td>Aggregates daily accounting (Linked to Transaction).</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<hr>

<h2>2. Corrected Cardinality Rules</h2>
<p>To fix the errors in the original diagram, apply the following rules:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Order Unification:</strong> Only ONE box for <code>orders</code>. branch out to <code>OrderItem</code>, <code>Payment</code>, <code>Invoice</code>, and <code>Delivery</code>.</li>
    <li><strong>Variant Selection:</strong> <code>OrderItem</code> must link to <code>CakeVariant</code> (N:1), not directly to <code>Cake</code>.</li>
    <li><strong>Cart Flow:</strong> <code>Customer</code> (1:1) -> <code>Cart</code> (1:N) -> <code>CartItem</code> (N:1) -> <code>CakeVariant</code>.</li>
    <li><strong>Feedback:</strong> <code>Order</code> (1:1) -> <code>Feedback</code>. This ensures one review per purchase.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>3. Technical Merchant Diagram (Mermaid Definition)</h2>
<p>Use the following text to generate a high-precision digital diagram:</p>

<div class="mermaid-desc">
erDiagram<br>
    CUSTOMER ||--o{ ORDERS : places<br>
    CUSTOMER ||--o| CART : has<br>
    CART ||--o{ CARTITEM : contains<br>
    CARTITEM }|--|| CAKEVARIANT : selects<br>
    ORDERS ||--o{ ORDERITEM : "composed of"<br>
    ORDERITEM }|--|| CAKEVARIANT : references<br>
    CAKEVARIANT }|--|| CAKE : "is variant of"<br>
    CAKE }|--|| CAKECATEGORY : "belongs to"<br>
    ORDERS ||--o| PAYMENT : "paid by"<br>
    ORDERS ||--o| DELIVERY : "shipped via"<br>
    ORDERS ||--o| INVOICE : "billed via"<br>
    ORDERS ||--o| FEEDBACK : "rated via"<br>
    PAYMENT ||--o{ TRANSACTION : generates<br>
    TRANSACTION }|--|| CASHBOOK : "logs into"<br>
    CUSTOMER ||--o{ NOTIFICATION : receives
</div>

<hr>

<p><em>End of Specification Report</em></p>

</body>
</html>
